cs.CL, cs.AI, cs.LG, cs.IR, cs.NE 

This paper is about improving open-domain conversational agents using natural language processing techniques. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.CL (Computation and Language). The paper also uses machine learning models, which suggests that it could belong to cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) or cs.LG (Learning). Additionally, the paper involves optimizing for coherence and diversity, which could fall under cs.IR (Information Retrieval) or cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing).
